[SN]TITLE[SN]
Snowdonia walker rescued after collapsing on footpath

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Mountain rescue volunteers and a coastguard helicopter were called out on Monday after a man collapsed on a footpath in Snowdonia.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
He became unwell at Llyn Idwal and injured his face in a fall.
He was treated at the scene, placed on a stretcher and carried to the helicopter which had landed close by on Cwm Idwal.
Ogwen Valley rescue team members also attended the incident.
